{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Fire|type2=Fighting}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Infernape}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Fire|prevnum=391|prev=Monferno|nextnum=393|next=Piplup|round=none}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Infernape}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Infernape\n|jname=ゴウカザル\n|tmname=Goukazaru\n|ndex=392\n|sdex=006\n|abrow=170\n|obrow=196\n|opbrow=205\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Fire\n|type2=Fighting\n|category=Flame\n|height-ftin=3\'11"\n|height-m=1.2\n|weight-lbs=121.3\n|weight-kg=55.0\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Blaze\n|abilityd=Iron Fist\n|egggroupn=2\n|egggroup1=Field\n|egggroup2=Human-Like\n|eggcycles=20\n|evtotal=3\n|evat=1\n|evsa=1\n|evsp=1\n|expyield=240\n|oldexp=209\n|lv100exp=1,059,860\n|gendercode=31\n|color=Brown\n|catchrate=45\n|body=06\n|pokefordex=infernape\n|generation=4\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Infernape\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'ゴウカザル\'\'\' \'\'Goukazaru\'\') is a dual-type {{2t|Fire|Fighting}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation IV]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolves]] from {{p|Monferno}} starting at [[level]] 36. It is the final form of {{p|Chimchar}}.\n\n==Biology==\nInfernape is a bipedal, primate-like Pokémon that is primarily reddish-brown with sections of white fur on its chest, head, and lower legs. Several gold markings adorn its body: swirled, circular ones on its knees and shoulders flame-shaped ones on the back of its hands, and a stripe around its back that forms two swirls on its chest. On top of its head is a large flame, which is never extinguished. Infernape has an orange, rounded muzzle, long, round ears with blue inside, and a red ridge over its eyes. The eyes themselves are blue with yellow sclerae. There are five blue digits on both its feet and hands, and it has a long tail. This quick Pokémon practices a unique kind of martial art that involves all of its limbs. This style uses fiery punches and kicks as well.\n\n==In the anime==\n===In the main series===\n[[File:Ash Infernape.png|250px|thumb|left|Infernape in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n====Major appearances====\n=====[[Ash\'s Infernape]]=====\nInfernape made its main series debut in \'\'[[DP163|Fighting Ire With Fire!]]\'\', when {{Ash}}\'s Monferno evolved into it while saving [[Ash\'s Pikachu]], [[Dawn\'s Piplup]], [[Paul\'s Electabuzz]], and [[Barry\'s Empoleon]] from {{TRT}}\'s falling [[Team Rocket\'s mechas|mecha]].\n\n=====[[Flint\'s Infernape]]=====\nAn Infernape belonging to {{EF|Flint}} appeared in \'\'[[DP165|Flint Sparks the Fire!]]\'\'. It then reappeared in \'\'[[DP180|Four Roads Diverged in a Pokémon Port!]]\'\' and \'\'[[DP191|Memories are Made of Bliss!]]\'\'.\n\n=====Other=====\nInfernape debuted in \'\'[[M10|The Rise of Darkrai]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Allegra]]. It {{pkmn|battle}}d against [[Brock\'s Croagunk]], and alongside [[Maury]]\'s {{p|Torterra}} and {{OBP|Kai|M10}}\'s {{p|Empoleon}} to stop the consequences of {{mov|Dialga}} and {{mov|Palkia}}\'s battle. It was later used in the [[Alamos Town]] [[Pokémon Contest]], where it helped Allegra win a [[Ribbon]].\n\n====Minor appearances====\n\n====Pokédex entries====\n{{Animedexheader|Sinnoh}}\n{{Animedexbody|DP163|Infernape|Dawn\'s Pokédex|Infernape, the Flame Pokémon and the evolved form of Monferno. Infernape\'s fiery crown reflects its fiery nature, and its speed is unmatched.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Diamond & Pearl\'\'|Sinnoh}}\n\n===In the Pokémon Masters Animated Trailer===\n====[[Flint\'s Infernape]]====\nFlint\'s Infernape briefly appeared in the [[Pokémon Masters Animated Trailer]]. Alongside [[Skyla\'s Swanna]] and [[Acerola]]\'s {{p|Palossand}}, it battled [[Bettie]]\'s {{p|Pikachu}}, [[Iris]]\'s {{p|Haxorus}}, and {{ga|Barry}}\'s {{p|Piplup}}, but the outcome of the {{pkmn|battle}} was left unknown.\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Chimler.png|thumb|200px|Infernape in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Pocket Monsters Platinum: Aim to Be Battle King!! manga===\n{{main|Yū Shirogane\'s Infernape}}\n[[Yū Shirogane]] has an Infernape, which he received as a Chimchar.\n\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\n{{main|Chimler}}\nIn \'\'[[PS359|Stunning Staravia & Stinky Skuntank II]]\'\', {{adv|Pearl}}\'s {{p|Monferno}}, [[Chimler]], evolved into an Infernape in [[Veilstone City]] alongside {{adv|Diamond}}\'s [[Tru]].\n\n===In the Pokémon Diamond and Pearl Adventure! manga===\n{{main|Mitsumi\'s Infernape}}\nInfernape is the final form of [[Mitsumi]]\'s [[starter Pokémon]], {{p|Chimchar}}. It made its debut in \'\'[[DPA06|Beauty Contest: The Pokémon Super Contest!!]]\'\', where it represented its Trainer in a [[Beautiful (condition)|Beauty]] Contest.\n\n===In the Pokémon + Nobunaga\'s Ambition ~ Ranse\'s Color Picture Scroll ~ manga===\nAn Infernape appeared in \'\'[[PNA5|The Blue Scroll: Mitsunari, Kiyomasa, and Masanori]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Hideyoshi]].\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Infernape (TCG)}}\n\n==Other appearances==\n===[[Super Smash Bros. for Nintendo 3DS/Wii U|Super Smash Bros. for Wii U]]===\nInfernape appears in the background in the {{st|Kalos Pokémon League}} stage. It appears in the {{DL|Pokémon League (Kalos)|Blazing Chamber}} along with other {{type|Fire}} Pokémon, namely {{p|Tepig}}, {{p|Blaziken}}, and {{p|Pyroar}}.\n\n====Trophy information====\n\'\'\'NA\'\'\': \'\'Infernape\'s flames burn like a raging inferno - that\'s probably how it got its name. The fire on its head never goes out, and the flames on its hands and feet, combined with its unique skills, make Infernape look like it\'s performing some kind of elaborate fire dance when it fights.\'\'\n\n\'\'\'PAL\'\'\': \'\'Doesn\'t the name just conjure up images of this fair creature living a peaceful life in a forest of ferns? You know, In-fern-ape. ...What, you think it\'s actually to do with "inferno"? Hmm... Well, maybe... Anyway, it has a crown of fire that never goes out, and combines flames and fighting in a way that looks like some kind of fire dance.\'\'\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=Fire|type2=fighting}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=IV}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=IV|reg1=Sinnoh|num1=006|reg2=Johto}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Diamond|entry=It uses a special kind of martial arts involving {{m|Close Combat|all its limbs}}. Its fire never goes out.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Pearl|entry=Its crown of fire is indicative of its fiery nature. It is beaten by none in terms of quickness.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Platinum|entry=It uses unique fighting moves with fire on its {{m|Fire Punch|hands}} and {{m|Blaze Kick|feet}}. It will take on any opponent.}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=HeartGold|v2=SoulSilver|entry=It tosses its enemies around with agility. It uses all its limbs to fight in its own unique style.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/1|gen=V|reg1=Unova}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Black|v2=White|t=FFF|entry=It uses unique fighting moves with fire on its hands and feet. It will take on any opponent.}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Black 2|v2=White 2|t=FFF|entry=It uses unique fighting moves with fire on its hands and feet. It will take on any opponent.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VI|reg1=Kalos|reg2=Hoenn}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=X|t=FFF|entry=Its crown of fire is indicative of its fiery nature. It is beaten by none in terms of quickness.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Y|entry=It tosses its enemies around with agility. It uses all its limbs to fight in its own unique style.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Omega Ruby|t=fff|entry=Its crown of fire is indicative of its fiery nature. It is beaten by none in terms of quickness.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Alpha Sapphire|t=FFF|entry=It tosses its enemies around with agility. It uses all its limbs to fight in its own unique style.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VII|reg1=Alola|reg2=Kanto}}\n{{Dex/NE|[[Generation VII]]}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Footer}}\n\n===Game locations===\n{{Availability/Header|type=Fire|type2=Fighting}}\n{{Availability/NA|gen=IV}}\n{{Availability/Gen|gen=IV}}\n{{Availability/Entry2|v=Diamond|v2=Pearl|area=[[Evolution|Evolve]] {{p|Monfern